replies.body:
I personally kind of like the idea but, perhaps the champ could do some kind of escape like ability to help their ally however not in a way similar to tahm, maybe more like a thresh w where you are able to help a teammate change their position in a less safe but faster way then Tahm but also maybe with more of a focus on helping to start a fight or bring a champ into the fight instead of keeping them away from the fight. It could work as a replacement for the q as if you want to have a true focus on the idea of a mobile support, Whatever the decision I find her very intersting, though just a tip


To me personally one of the champions who feels the most nimble is Jinx after getting a kill in the middle of a team fight, she doesn't gain cc immunity or even any form of dash but if the movement speed is a massive boost and the animation is good you can feel nimble and fast without having to actually rely on dash or blinks, The new Quinn also gives off this feeling in that your ult a level 16 makes you feel crazy fast but if you get hit by minions even though you only go down to the normal movement speed for quinn you feel slow because of how its communicated to you.


Best of Luck{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}
